    "body": "Ok this is not a working setup... VPN connectivity results in max 2 or 3 peers... All the port forwardings and bindings and port magics does not work for me. How can i host a lighthouse behind a VPN Server?\r\n\r\nhere are my current before.rules of my vpn server. This is already working great in some other projects.\r\n\r\n```\r\n# Ethereum goerli\r\n# listen\r\n-A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p tcp --dport 30303 -j DNAT --to-destination 10.8.0.8:30303\r\n# discovery\r\n-A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p udp --dport 30303 -j DNAT --to-destination 10.8.0.8:30303\r\n\r\n# Ethereum 2.0 sigp/lighthouse Project\r\n-A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p tcp --dport 9000 -j DNAT --to-destination 10.8.0.8:9000\r\n-A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p udp --dport 9000 -j DNAT --to-destination 10.8.0.8:9000\r\n-A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p tcp --dport 13000 -j DNAT --to-destination 10.8.0.8:13000\r\n-A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p udp --dport 12000 -j DNAT --to-destination 10.8.0.8:12000\r\n\r\n# Allow traffic from OpenVPN client to eth0 (change to the interface you discovered!)\r\n-A POSTROUTING -s 10.8.0.0/24 -o eth0 -j MASQUERADE\r\nCOMMIT\r\n# END OPENVPN RULES\r\n```\r\ngoerli gets parameterized with --nat extpip = external ip, beacon node with --listen-address = tun0 ip\r\n\r\n// meanwhile i got successfull setup geth via openvpn and reached my maxpeers. my configurations basically works but not for lighthouse. maybe its impact from discv5?",
